{"TopicId":145197,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"EVA Kerbals not staying put on ladders","CreatedByName":"AmenRa","CreatedById":144877,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-01T11:33:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"AmenRa","CreatedById":144877,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-01T11:33:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nKSP: 1.1.3 (Win64) - Unity: 5.2.4f1 - OS: Windows 10\u00A0 (10.0.0) 64bit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nKerbal Inventory System - 1.2.12\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nKSP-AVC Plugin - 1.1.6.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nInfernal Robots - 2.0.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nSCANsat - 1.1.6.3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nTarsierSpaceTechnology - 6.4\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nAnyone having issues with Kerbals not staying put on\u00A0ladders?\u00A0I am find it very frustrating that the Kerbals do not stay fixed to ladders when performing EVA\u0027s. The Kerbal either slides up or down the ladder or, just eventually lets go for no reason.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nI am using the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E (Kerbal Inventory System - 1.2.12) to build stations. It is extremely frustrating during times when I need more than one Kerbal in EVA to move parts because the Kerbals just\u00A0keep floating off and eventually get out of range. They won\u0027t stay put on the ladders mounted to the station.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in .0001pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-01T11:34:19Z\u0022 title=\u002208/01/2016 11:34  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 1, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by AmenRa\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"aluc24","CreatedById":152712,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-03T12:59:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also have this problem. It would be great if someone could give a comment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-03T13:09:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222702755\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145197\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470229159\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152712\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022aluc24\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, aluc24 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also have this problem. It would be great if someone could give a comment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEither nobody else has this issue anymore, or people just got used to this annoying thing that has been around forever. I seem to recal at one point people even exploited the weird kerbal/ladder thing for propulsion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs far as I can tell nothing has been done about this and kerbals still slide off ladders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}